msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:45
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Solution:</emphasis> In &kmail;, choose "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guisubmenu>Configure KMail</"
"guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Identities</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>(Choose an "
"identity)</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Modify</"
"guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Advanced</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Sent-mail "
"folder</guimenuitem></menuchoice>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid "How to store trash mails in a special folder?"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:51
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Symptom:</emphasis> You want to store mails in a special folder. "
"Maybe you are using an &IMAP; server and want Trashed mails to be stored on "
"the server, not in the client."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the settings dialog select an &IMAP; account on the <guilabel>Accounts</"
"guilabel> page. Click on <guibutton>Modify</guibutton> and change the trash "
"folder location on the <guilabel>Advanced</guilabel> tab."
